Troops of 31 Artillery Brigade have neutralised some bandits and rescued seven abducted victims in Niger State. The crushing of the bandits was carried out by troops deployed for “Operation Whirl Punch” during a mop-up exercise to clear bandits at Dogon Gona Forest in Niger State. In a statement issued by the coordinator, Defence Media Operations, Major John Enenche, said that the victims were abandoned by the bandits after a fierce battle. He said that the victims were allegedly kidnapped on 27th March, 2020 and taken to an unknown destination. “Following interrogation after a successful rescue operation, the village head of Madak,i confirmed that the victims were natives of Roro Village of Shiroro local government area of  Niger State,” he said. Enenche said that the victims would soon be handed over to the appropriate authorities for necessary action. Also, on the same day, he said that the troops at Kontokoro Village on clearance operation neutralised several bandits while others escaped with gunshot wounds after a fierce battle.  